<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1893-09-25T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1893-09-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="458" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d458">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Adee</persName> to Señor
                                    <persName type="to">Romero</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1893-09-25"><hi rend="italic">September 25,
                                    1893</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the
                            receipt of your note of the 6th instant relative to the alleged
                            violation of Mexican territory through the arrest at Nogales, Mexico, by
                            John Roberts, deputy sheriff at Nogales, Ariz., of Jesus Garcia, a
                            citizen of Mexico.</p>
                        <p>The governor of Arizona Territory has been asked to cause a searching
                            investigation and to report the facts.</p>
                        <p>Accept, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Alvey A. Adee</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>